Busia and Uganda security chiefs on Tuesday held a five-hour meeting to find solutions to cross-border land disputes between residents of Mayenje in Kenya and Buyengo in Uganda.Busia county commissioner John Chelimo said the two communities have been fighting over the swampy area.Hussein Kato Matanda, the resident district commissioner Busia, Uganda, said the two countries will send surveyors to establish a clear boundary to end the conflict.